timeline.bodyText:
The previous behavior was to also call end() when an exception is thrown. Since end() is only actually executed on when the UoW commits, it leaves it up to the configuration to decide whether the exception is a reason to roll back.
So I suggest:
try {
    Object result = super.handle(message, target);
} finally {
    Sagalifecycle.end();
}

